00:50:41.394 --> 00:50:55.280
If God can do it for the Greens and Hobby Lobby with a creative idea that started out of his garage, how much more can God do it for you?

00:51:01.787 --> 00:51:06.301
You could be the best pie maker in the whole thing and you go, "Hey, you know what?

00:51:06.301 --> 00:51:08.079
God gave me the best recipe.

00:51:09.324 --> 00:51:10.569
I got it out of prayer.

00:51:14.640 --> 00:51:14.880
I saw it in a vision.

00:51:14.880 --> 00:51:25.031
" And the Lord said, "If you just add this and this and this and you just put this and it's the best pie.

00:51:25.636 --> 00:51:31.355
" You know, Coca-Cola, nobody can figure out their formula forever.

00:51:31.355 --> 00:51:35.520
How do you make it?

00:51:35.520 --> 00:51:46.414
Or Colonel Sanders' original recipe when he went to a Kathryn Kuhlman meeting.

00:51:46.414 --> 00:51:56.057
He didn't know if it was real or not.

00:51:59.370 --> 00:51:59.680
And Kathryn Kuhlman prayed for him.

00:51:59.680 --> 00:52:02.700
He fell out in the Holy Ghost.

00:52:02.700 --> 00:52:05.200
Billy was telling us about it.

00:52:05.200 --> 00:52:08.880
He said Kathryn Kuhlman prayed for Colonel Sanders.

00:52:08.880 --> 00:52:11.440
She called him the chicken man.

00:52:27.146 --> 00:52:27.582
Thank God for Kentucky Fried Chicken.

00:52:27.582 --> 00:52:30.213
He was a giver.

00:52:41.714 --> 00:52:42.160
Father, we thank you, Lord, for the better original recipe.

00:52:46.640 --> 00:52:48.560
You give it to us, Father, because you know what makes things taste good.

00:52:49.200 --> 00:52:52.640
You know, God, how to make a better car.

00:52:53.940 --> 00:52:56.819
You know how to make a better lawn mower that runs better.

00:55:25.506 --> 00:55:29.075
I don't know.

00:55:29.075 --> 00:56:05.119
Father, I thank you that you're giving creative ideas to your people tonight.

00:56:14.076 --> 00:56:32.452
And Father, when they lay their head on the pillow, they sleep soundly but they have dreams and they are able to see things ahead of time.

00:57:08.390 --> 00:57:08.760
And God, we are the trendsetters.

00:57:08.760 --> 00:57:24.569
You give us better ideas than what the world has because we're led by the Spirit and we take this body in the name of Jesus.

00:57:24.569 --> 00:57:35.306
Amen and amen.

00:58:41.360 --> 00:58:43.759
You believe it.

00:58:43.759 --> 00:58:45.871
It's time to believe.

00:58:56.400 --> 00:58:56.827
I believe.

00:58:56.827 --> 00:59:01.170
I receive everything the Lord has for me.

00:59:01.790 --> 00:59:59.920
And I take the blood and we make much of the blood and the blood makes much of us.

00:59:59.920 --> 01:00:01.420
I thank you, Lord.

01:00:01.420 --> 01:00:03.386
We repent of our sins.

01:00:03.386 --> 01:00:12.519
We thank you, Lord, that you are faithful and just to forgive us of our sins and cleanse us of all unrighteousness.

01:00:12.519 --> 01:00:23.851
We take this blood right now in Jesus' name.

01:00:23.851 --> 01:00:35.040
And we give you all the glory, honor, and praise for it in the name of Jesus.

01:00:35.040 --> 01:00:36.940
Amen and amen.

01:00:36.940 --> 01:00:37.860
Right.

01:00:37.860 --> 01:00:53.270
You want some of my water?

01:02:07.493 --> 01:02:07.706
You can read some of that.

01:02:07.706 --> 01:02:09.639
Where did you leave off?

01:02:09.639 --> 01:02:12.820
Let her read to you a little bit.

01:02:12.820 --> 01:02:18.096
I love to hear some of this book and we'll pray over these wells.

01:02:18.096 --> 01:02:23.140
We still got a little bit of time here.

01:02:23.140 --> 01:02:24.939
You ain't going.

01:02:24.939 --> 01:02:32.799
If you want to click out, you can.

01:02:50.160 --> 01:02:52.305
But I like reading a little bit.

01:02:52.305 --> 01:03:11.109
It changes the atmosphere.

01:03:11.119 --> 01:03:55.599
There's such a blessing on books that are anointed.

01:03:55.599 --> 01:05:20.732
'You want to be used mightily, then be willing to be hidden.

01:05:20.732 --> 01:05:44.760
God often conceals his most powerful weapons.

01:07:30.879 --> 01:07:31.199
He tucks them away in upper rooms, in closets, in wildernesses because they're too dangerous for the applause of man.

01:07:34.720 --> 01:07:35.040
I lived hidden.

01:07:35.040 --> 01:07:38.995
I died hidden.

01:07:38.995 --> 01:07:50.720
And yet my prayers still echo eternity.

01:07:50.720 --> 01:07:59.779
Hidden intercession is not a punishment.

01:08:07.404 --> 01:08:07.662
It's a promotion.

01:08:08.400 --> 01:08:11.990
When God hides you, he's trusting you to carry something sacred.

01:08:15.839 --> 01:08:16.410
I prayed in towns I would never see again.

01:08:27.280 --> 01:08:27.840
I laid foundations for revivals that would come after I died.

01:08:27.840 --> 01:08:31.564
That's the mark of true intercession.

01:08:31.564 --> 01:08:37.233
It builds altars for the next generation to burn upon.

01:08:39.839 --> 01:08:41.679
You may never see the fruit, but the fire will fall.

01:08:41.679 --> 01:08:45.542
Stop asking, "What did I build?

01:08:45.542 --> 01:08:47.897
" Start asking, "Did I obey?

01:08:47.897 --> 01:08:51.613
" Faithfulness is measured in eternity, not Instagram likes.

01:08:51.613 --> 01:09:50.514
When Finney stood before thousands, I stood before God.

01:09:50.514 --> 01:10:00.149
When he gave the altar call, I stood at the heavenly gates pleading for mercy.

01:10:00.149 --> 01:10:02.937
When he rested, I wrestled.

01:10:16.800 --> 01:10:17.056
You may feel unseen, but you are known in the courts of heaven.

01:10:18.080 --> 01:10:23.973
And when you step into eternity, you'll discover that your hidden life was a highway for revival.

01:10:23.973 --> 01:10:27.668
There's a sound that doesn't come from the mouth.

01:10:33.939 --> 01:10:34.199
It comes from the spirit.

01:10:34.199 --> 01:10:36.205
It's the sound of travail.

01:10:36.205 --> 01:10:41.560
It's the cry of a soul in sync with the heartbeat of God.

01:10:45.120 --> 01:10:45.480
And I'll tell you this, that sound shakes principalities.

01:10:45.480 --> 01:10:56.773
I've heard demons scream in the spirit realm when a true intercessor groaned under the weight of divine burden.

01:10:56.773 --> 01:11:01.730
You don't have to yell to terrorize darkness.

01:11:01.730 --> 01:11:03.959
Hell doesn't fear volume.

01:11:25.143 --> 01:11:25.474
It fears authority.

01:11:26.800 --> 01:11:28.743
And authority comes from intimacy.

01:11:28.743 --> 01:12:07.040
When you pray with heaven's permission and the spirit's power, even your whispers become weapons.

01:12:18.640 --> 01:12:19.040
I wasn't trying to impress heaven.

01:12:19.040 --> 01:12:21.653
I was trying to move it.

01:12:21.653 --> 01:12:23.556
I didn't come to intercession with formulas.

01:12:23.556 --> 01:12:24.909
I came with desperation.

01:12:25.670 --> 01:12:29.257
And when your desperation becomes holy, it turns into something beautiful.

01:12:52.140 --> 01:12:52.360
A sound that bends the heavens.

01:14:09.911 --> 01:14:10.053
It's the sound of Jesus in Gethsemane.

01:14:19.160 --> 01:14:19.450
The sound of Hannah in the temple.

01:14:22.719 --> 01:14:23.051
The sound of the spirit groaning through yielded vessels.

01:14:24.045 --> 01:14:28.290
That sound terrifies every power of darkness.

01:14:28.290 --> 01:14:32.811
When you truly walk in prevailing intercession, you become a mobile altar.

01:14:32.811 --> 01:14:38.548
Demons sense you before you say a word.

01:14:38.548 --> 01:14:40.640
Environments shift when you enter rooms.

01:14:40.640 --> 01:14:44.510
Your spirit carries residue from the secret place.

01:14:45.634 --> 01:14:47.143
And everything unclean takes notice.

01:14:49.474 --> 01:14:49.851
This isn't religion.

01:14:57.467 --> 01:14:57.680
This is war.

01:14:59.291 --> 01:14:59.485
And your groan is your battle cry.

01:15:21.463 --> 01:15:21.829
I reached places in intercession where I was no longer praying.

01:15:24.251 --> 01:15:24.674
I was being prayed through.

01:15:24.674 --> 01:15:36.237
My mind was still, but the groans came like waves.

01:15:36.237 --> 01:15:44.925
The spirit took over.

01:15:44.925 --> 01:15:46.639
I became a vessel.

01:15:46.639 --> 01:15:47.920
My words left.

01:15:47.920 --> 01:15:49.154
My will surrendered.

01:16:01.874 --> 01:16:02.263
And in those holy moments, I felt like I touched the edge of eternity.

01:16:02.263 --> 01:16:05.040
That's where real intercession begins.

01:16:05.040 --> 01:16:08.090
You don't push your agenda.

01:16:08.090 --> 01:16:09.840
You host his.

01:16:09.840 --> 01:16:12.879
You don't ask for things.

01:16:12.879 --> 01:16:19.440
You become a conduit for his divine will.

01:18:12.640 --> 01:18:28.239
The spirit searches the mind of God and pours it through you like fire down a pipe.

01:18:28.239 --> 01:19:07.990
I remember times I'd be walking and suddenly feel a crushing weight fall on my soul.

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:14.999
I'd collapse in prayer, often in unexpected places.

01:20:06.907 --> 01:21:02.630
The Lord would drop a burden on me so heavy I couldn't move until it lifted.

01:21:02.640 --> 01:21:25.066
That's not emotionalism.

01:21:25.066 --> 01:21:32.620
That's spiritual possession—not by a demon, but by the Holy Ghost.

01:21:32.620 --> 01:21:43.700
God is looking for people he can trust with his burden.

01:21:43.700 --> 01:22:00.285
Not people who will treat it like a goosebump, but like a baby in the womb—something that must be carried until it's birthed in the earth.

01:22:00.285 --> 01:22:05.488
' I love that.

01:22:05.488 --> 01:22:16.727
It's carrying it in prayer until it's birthed in the earth.

01:23:19.920 --> 01:23:20.286
I said because you're never going to get what you're wanting in the natural until you birth it in the spirit.

01:23:20.286 --> 01:23:32.263
It comes through the spirit first and then birthed through travail, right?

01:23:32.263 --> 01:23:40.510
Through intercession.

01:23:40.510 --> 01:23:46.840
Keep going.

01:23:46.840 --> 01:24:25.719
'I didn't need to prepare fancy words.

01:24:25.719 --> 01:24:33.633
I didn't need eloquence.

01:24:49.440 --> 01:24:50.187
I just needed yieldedness.

01:24:50.187 --> 01:24:58.856
When the spirit prays through you, everything changes.

01:24:58.856 --> 01:25:01.574
Chains break.

01:25:01.574 --> 01:25:04.415
Atmospheres shift.

01:25:04.415 --> 01:25:07.020
Glory falls.

01:25:07.020 --> 01:25:10.419
That's because it's no longer you.

01:25:12.639 --> 01:25:16.640
It's God interceding through you.

01:25:16.640 --> 01:25:21.075
That kind of intercession breaks regions.

01:25:30.310 --> 01:25:30.800
The prophet Joel described it best: Let the priest weep between the porch and the altar.

01:25:30.800 --> 01:25:35.195
That image never left me.

01:25:35.195 --> 01:25:43.969
That place between the entryway and the holy fire is where revival begins.

01:25:52.280 --> 01:25:52.480
It's where the tears fall.

01:25:52.480 --> 01:25:57.993
It's where repentance flows.

01:25:57.993 --> 01:26:15.893
It's where intercessors cry out with desperation.

01:26:17.991 --> 01:26:28.110
I wept in many places, but the most powerful tears fell when I prayed for the church to awaken.

01:26:28.110 --> 01:26:55.040
God honors the tears of intercessors more than the applause of preachers.

01:26:55.040 --> 01:27:04.450
There are natural tears and then there are spirit-born tears.

01:27:04.450 --> 01:27:15.144
' I didn't cry because I was emotional.

01:27:15.144 --> 01:27:41.189
I cried because the burden was so heavy it crushed my heart open.

01:27:41.199 --> 01:27:44.491
Those tears were prophetic.

01:27:44.491 --> 01:27:51.590
They carried the weight of regions.

01:27:51.600 --> 01:28:49.510
They were mixed with heaven's grief and heaven's hope.

01:28:49.520 --> 01:29:31.000
Sometimes a single tear from an intercessor does more than ten sermons ever could.

01:29:31.000 --> 01:29:39.600
That in-between place, the porch and the altar, is a posture.

01:29:39.600 --> 01:29:59.346
You've come close enough to the presence to be transformed, but you're still standing in the gap for others.

01:30:36.675 --> 01:30:39.452
You haven't stepped into glory for yourself.

01:30:39.452 --> 01:30:54.952
You're pulling others in with your tears.

01:30:54.952 --> 01:31:07.215
That place is painful, but it's also holy.

01:32:16.159 --> 01:32:18.342
And that is where revival is born.

01:33:03.600 --> 01:33:15.020
Lord, take me to the place between the porch and the altar.

01:33:15.020 --> 01:33:20.580
Let my heart break with yours.

01:33:20.580 --> 01:34:11.419
Make me an intercessor who bleeds in prayer for the sake of the church and the world.

01:34:11.419 --> 01:34:13.280
Give me tears that carry glory.

01:34:13.280 --> 01:34:15.760
Let my weeping birth revival.

01:34:15.760 --> 01:34:17.813
Let my sorrow become intercession.

01:34:17.813 --> 01:34:23.531
I will not run from the weight; I welcome it.

01:34:23.531 --> 01:34:31.360
I just pretend like I'm in the car when you read to me.

01:35:29.120 --> 01:35:29.720
I love to hear it, Diana.

01:35:36.928 --> 01:35:37.472
It just fans the flame.

01:35:37.472 --> 01:36:07.376
If you're dry, if you've got to inspire yourself, be inspired to pray.

01:36:07.376 --> 01:36:16.000
What motivates you to jump in that river?

01:36:16.000 --> 01:36:27.176
Grab a hold of things that help you because the dryness of the world continually tries to drain us.

01:36:27.176 --> 01:36:42.560
But when you fan that flame for prayer, you realize this is what motivates us.

01:36:42.560 --> 01:36:49.233
We're making a difference.

01:36:49.233 --> 01:36:56.960
Every single one of us, as we come together and we intercede for the nations.

01:36:56.960 --> 01:37:06.272
Some people don't have that motivation.

01:37:06.272 --> 01:37:25.189
This is the book.

01:37:25.199 --> 01:37:37.520
It's like going to the gym.

01:37:37.520 --> 01:38:21.008
Some people have it and you look at them and say, 'How do you look so chiseled?

01:38:21.008 --> 01:38:23.760
You're so motivated.

01:38:23.760 --> 01:38:39.066
' And then there are some people that are just not motivated.

01:38:39.066 --> 01:38:48.240
If I were motivated, I'd look like that, too.

01:38:48.240 --> 01:38:51.119
It takes work.

01:38:51.119 --> 01:39:13.669
What motivates them to do it?

01:39:13.679 --> 01:39:25.851
How did they get there?

01:39:25.851 --> 01:40:22.300
They feed on stuff that motivates them.

01:40:22.300 --> 01:42:10.393
How do you become a spiritual giant, to look like somebody that's ripped in the spirit realm?

01:42:20.066 --> 01:42:20.755
You motivate yourself.

01:42:23.520 --> 01:42:33.657
And the only way you do that is by what you choose to feed on.

01:42:33.657 --> 01:42:40.371
What am I putting in me?

01:42:40.371 --> 01:42:51.037
People go, 'Well, you're there because of this.

01:42:51.037 --> 01:43:00.906
' No, I choose to go to that gym.

01:43:00.906 --> 01:43:05.910
So, we'll just pray now.

01:43:05.920 --> 01:43:29.832
Thank you for reading a little bit there to us.

01:43:29.832 --> 01:43:37.564
Father, we just lift up this time before you.

01:43:37.564 --> 01:43:40.739
We're going to jump in that river.

01:43:40.739 --> 01:43:42.720
Is it not working?

01:43:46.560 --> 01:43:50.574
I'm sorry.

01:43:50.574 --> 01:44:25.516
Some like the microphone, some hate it, but it costs a lot, so I use it.

01:45:16.435 --> 01:45:27.750
Father, we just thank you, Lord.

01:45:27.760 --> 01:45:31.226
We're just yielded to you, Holy Spirit.

01:45:39.307 --> 01:45:46.269
You said to pray over these wells, and we're going to pray over them now.

01:45:46.269 --> 01:46:01.339
Father, I thank you that you show us the exact way to bring this down because without you, we can't do this.

01:46:01.339 --> 01:46:11.635
We need you in every aspect of our life.

01:46:11.635 --> 01:46:21.733
You said they're going to attack the infrastructure of our nation.

01:46:21.733 --> 01:46:38.813
You said, 'Pray over this for disruptions to be brought to justice.

01:46:38.813 --> 01:47:08.390
' Father, I thank you that as we come together as believers who are bold over this, I yield to the anointing that you've called me to walk in.

01:47:31.726 --> 01:47:32.069
And I thank you, Father, uninterrupted and unhindered by any satanic or demonic force.

01:47:32.069 --> 01:47:38.000
We praise you and we give this prayer time to you.

01:47:38.000 --> 01:47:44.000
We pray for the next hour and we lift up the nation before you.

01:47:44.000 --> 01:47:49.531
We pray for our president.

01:47:49.531 --> 01:47:54.613
We pray for Israel.

01:47:54.613 --> 01:48:00.029
We pray for the things that need prayer.

01:48:00.029 --> 01:48:04.194
I'm seeing the men in the apartment complex again.

01:48:07.315 --> 01:48:07.520
It's all on the walls.

01:48:14.280 --> 01:48:16.506
The planned attack is on the walls of the apartment and blueprints.

01:48:16.506 --> 01:48:18.579
They have pictures of it.

01:48:32.510 --> 01:48:32.920
It looks like drone footage.

01:48:43.208 --> 01:48:46.711
I see a river, a stream of water that is attached to this facility that they're looking at.

01:48:46.711 --> 01:48:51.880
It's a waterway used for cooling, but I see this boat.

01:48:51.880 --> 01:49:00.160
They're in a boat and they're casing it out from the boat.

01:49:00.160 --> 01:49:06.335
They've taken a tube; it's PVC, like the pipes that you get at Lowe's.

01:49:06.335 --> 01:49:12.112
And they've made a launcher out of a tube.

01:49:12.112 --> 01:49:14.800
It looks like a homemade launcher.

01:49:31.679 --> 01:49:32.399
I see this tube that looks like you put something down in it and light the fuse, and it shoots it off like a cannon.

01:49:33.120 --> 01:49:50.537
It's just a little metal boat, like you would get at Bass Pro Shop, with one of those cheap motors in the back.

01:49:50.537 --> 01:49:52.000
This is a cheap-looking boat.

01:49:52.000 --> 01:49:56.427
They don't even keep it close; they keep it on the shoreline, attached to a tree in the woods.

01:50:09.840 --> 01:50:10.173
There's a yellow line attaching this boat to a tree hidden in the woods, camouflaged.

01:50:10.173 --> 01:50:14.258
The pipe that they're using is about two inches around.

01:50:15.959 --> 01:50:16.159
It looks like a mortar round pipe.

01:50:18.880 --> 01:50:19.440
It's long but it's made to shoot projectiles out of it.

01:50:19.440 --> 01:50:27.828
It's a PVC pipe, white, and they've designed it for explosives to launch them where they want them to go.

01:50:27.828 --> 01:50:40.331
It's some kind of launching device on this boat.

01:50:40.331 --> 01:50:44.354
But they have more than one.

01:50:46.579 --> 01:50:49.280
The Lord says there are a lot of tourists.

01:51:00.360 --> 01:51:00.693
I see the tourists; they're all on the waterfront.

01:51:18.765 --> 01:51:19.028
They're scoping out a power plant.

01:51:19.028 --> 01:51:20.736
You see the stacks?

01:51:20.736 --> 01:51:25.371
You can see steam coming out of these tubes.

01:51:25.371 --> 01:51:31.720
I see one, two, three major stacks of power, like steam turbines.

01:51:31.720 --> 01:51:37.956
There is red at the top of these stacks, marked like you would see for pilots, like lights.

01:51:37.956 --> 01:51:39.760
They're power stacks, like chimneys.

01:51:39.760 --> 01:51:47.409
They're trying to make themselves look like fishermen.

01:51:48.860 --> 01:51:54.149
They want to be disguised as fishermen.

01:51:59.439 --> 01:51:59.706
It looks so innocent.

01:52:11.520 --> 01:52:12.400
They have those fisherman hats on and those vests where you put your lures.

01:52:28.769 --> 01:52:29.119
I see them in their boat; one is taking pictures and the other acts like he's fishing.

01:52:38.320 --> 01:52:38.549
They don't want to draw attention because they look like they're just fishermen.

01:52:38.549 --> 01:52:39.920
That's what they're wearing.

01:52:39.920 --> 01:52:44.680
They just look like fishermen with nets going down the river.

01:52:47.599 --> 01:52:51.560
But they're casing these places for tourists, casing the power plants, and casing our water supply.

01:52:51.560 --> 01:53:16.088
It's on a riverfront with a little black motor on the back of a metal boat, and they're fishing in the river.

01:53:16.088 --> 01:53:21.383
There are three men.

01:53:21.383 --> 01:53:36.016
One's steering it, one's in the middle, and one's at the end, all on the boat.

01:53:36.016 --> 01:53:38.220
Two separate accounts.

01:53:38.220 --> 01:53:45.920
One boat has two men at another place, and the other boat has three men.

01:53:45.920 --> 01:53:48.020
This is a bigger boat.

01:53:48.020 --> 01:54:18.310
But there are two different groups that I am seeing.

01:54:18.310 --> 01:54:32.760
One has one steering the boat and one is at the helm at the end of it, and he's acting like he's fishing, but they're scouting.

01:54:32.760 --> 01:54:36.046
They're going down the rivers; they're going down these streams.

01:54:36.046 --> 01:54:46.709
It looks like waterways, places of great water, but they're scoping things out.

01:55:07.497 --> 01:55:07.851
It's in surveillance; it doesn't look as mysterious if you're fishing.

